/wiki/Spain_women%27s_national_water_pol: The Spain women's national water polo team represents Spain in women's international water polo competitions and it is controlled by Real Federación Española de Natación.
/wiki/Marta_Bach: Marta Bach Pascual (born 1993) is a Spanish female water polo player. She is 5 ft 9 inches tall.
/wiki/Andrea_Blas: Andrea Blas Martinez (born 14 February 1992 in Zaragoza) is a Spanish female water polo player. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she competed for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event, where they won the silver medal. She is 5 ft 8 inches tall.
/wiki/Anna_Espar: Anna Espar Llaquet (born January 8, 1993) is a Spanish female water polo player who won the gold medal at the 2013 World Championships in Barcelona.
/wiki/Laura_Ester: Laura Ester Ramos (born 22 January 1990, Barcelona) is a Spanish female water polo goalkeeper. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she competed for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event, winning the silver medal.  She also competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics.  She is 5 ft 7 inches tall.
/wiki/Maica_Garc%C3%ADa_Godoy: María del Carmen "Maica" García Godoy born (1990-10-17)October 17, 1990 in Barcelona, Spain is a Spanish female water polo player, playing at the centre forward position. She is part of the Spain women's national water polo team. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she won a silver medal competing for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event. She is 6 ft 2 in (1.88 m) tall. She plays for the Spanish club CN Sabadell.
/wiki/Patricia_Herrera: Patricia Herrera Fernandez (born 9 February 1993) is a female water polo goalkeeper of Spain.
/wiki/Laura_L%C3%B3pez_(water_polo): Laura López Ventosa (born 13 January 1988) is a Spanish female water polo player. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she competed for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event, where they won the silver medal. She is 5 ft 7 in (1.70 m) inches tall.
/wiki/Ona_Meseguer: Ona Meseguer Flaqué (born 20 February 1988) is a Spanish female water polo player.  At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she competed for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event winning the silver medal. She is 5 ft 6 inches tall.
/wiki/Lorena_Miranda: Lorena Miranda Dorado (1991) is a Spanish female water polo player. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she competed for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event, winning the silver medal. She is 5 ft 8.5 inches tall.
/wiki/Matilde_Ortiz: Matilde Ortiz Reyes (born 16 September 1990 in Veracruz, Mexico) is a Spanish female water polo player. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she won a silver medal competing for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event. She is 5 ft 8.5 inches tall. She plays for the Spanish club CN Sabadell, and is studying journalism at the Autonomous University of Barcelona.
/wiki/Jennifer_Pareja: Jennifer Pareja Lisalde (born 8 May 1984) is a former Spanish female water polo player who won the gold medal at the 2013 World Championships in Barcelona, being named Most Valuable Player of the event.
/wiki/Pilar_Pe%C3%B1a_Carrasco: María del Pilar Peña Carrasco (born 4 April 1986) is a Spanish female water polo player. She was born in Madrid, and played for Club Natación Ondarreta Alcorcón, who won the Spanish championship in 2006, and the Spanish cup in 2006 and 2007.  At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she won a silver medal competing for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event. She is 5 ft 7.5 inches tall. She now plays for the Spanish club CN Sabadell, with whom she won the Spanish championship in 2011, 2012 and 2013.
/wiki/Roser_Tarrag%C3%B3: Roser Tarragó Aymerich (born March 25, 1993) is a Spanish female water polo player. At the 2012 Summer Olympics, she competed for the Spain women's national water polo team in the women's event, where they won the silver medal.
/wiki/Water_polo_at_the_2013_World_Aquat: Water polo in the 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held between 21 July – 3 August at Piscines Bernat Picornell in Barcelona, Spain.
The women's water polo tournament at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships, organised by the FINA, was held in the Piscines Bernat Picornell in Barcelona, Spain from 21 July to 2 August 2013.
/wiki/Clara_Basiana: 2006 SEVILLA Co.me.n Cup: silver medal TEAM, gold medal COMBO.
/wiki/Alba_Mar%C3%ADa_Cabello: Alba María Cabello Rodilla (born 30 April 1986) is a Spanish synchronized swimmer. She competed at the 2008 and 2012 Summer Olympics, winning a silver and a bronze respectively in the women's team event.
/wiki/Ona_Carbonell: Ona Carbonell Ballestero (born June 5, 1990) is a Spanish synchronized swimmer and sister to the famous Catalan poet and researcher Max Carbonell.
/wiki/Margalida_Cresp%C3%AD: Margalida Crespí Jaume (born 15 August 1990) is a Spanish competitor in synchronized swimming. She won a bronze medal in the team competition at the 2012 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Tha%C3%AFs_Henr%C3%ADquez: Thaïs Henríquez (born 29 October 1982) is a Spanish synchronized swimmer. She competed for Spain in the team event at the 2008 Summer Olympics, winning silver, and the 2012 Summer Olympics, winning bronze.
/wiki/Paula_Klamburg: Paula Klamburg (born 20 September 1989, Barcelona) is a retired Spanish competitor in synchronized swimming. She won a bronze medal in the team competition at the 2012 Summer Olympics.  She announced her retirement after Spanish team did not qualify for the 2016 Summer Olympics.  She began training in synchronised swimming in 1997 and made her international debut at the 2009 World Championships.
/wiki/Sara_Levy: Sara Levy Sellares (born 23 May 1994) is a Spanish competitor in synchronized swimming.
/wiki/Meritxell_Mas: Meritxell Mas Pujadas (born 25 December 1994) is a Spanish competitor in synchronised swimming.
/wiki/Cristina_Salvador: Cristina Salvador González (born 26 September 1991) is a Spanish competitor in synchronized swimming.
/wiki/Synchronised_swimming_at_the_2013_: The Synchronised swimming competition at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held from July 20 to July 27 at the Palau Sant Jordi, Barcelona, Spain.
The team technical routine competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 20–22 with the preliminary round on July 20 and the final on July 22.
/wiki/Laia_Pons: Laia Pons (24 April 1993) is a Spanish competitor in synchronized swimming. She won a bronze medal in team competition at the 2012 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Synchronised_swimming_at_the_2013_: The team free routine competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 23–26 with the preliminary round on July 23 and the final on July 26.
The free routine combination competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 21–27 with the preliminary round on July 21 and the final on July 27.
/wiki/Melanie_Costa: Melania Felicitas Costa Schmid, (born 24 April 1989), also known as Melani Costa, is a Spanish competition swimmer.
/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2013_World_Aquatic: The swimming events of the 15th FINA World Aquatics Championships were held July 28 – August 4, 2013, in Barcelona, Spain. The competition was held in a long course pool inside the Palau Sant Jordi. It featured 40 LCM events, split evenly between males and females. Swimming was one of the five aquatic disciplines at the championships.
The women's 400 meter freestyle event in swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships took place on 28 July at the Palau Sant Jordi in Barcelona, Spain.
/wiki/Mireia_Belmonte: Mireia Belmonte García (born 10 November 1990) is a Spanish Olympic, world, and European champion swimmer. She is the first female Olympic champion in the history of Spanish swimming and is widely considered to be the greatest Spanish swimmer of all time.
/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2013_World_Aquatic: The women's 200 metre butterfly event in swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships took place on 31 July and 1 August at the Palau Sant Jordi in Barcelona, Spain.
The women's 400 metre individual medley event in swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships took place on 4 August at the Palau Sant Jordi in Barcelona, Spain.
/wiki/Synchronised_swimming_at_the_2013_: The solo technical routine competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 20 with the preliminary round in the morning and the final in the evening session.
The Duet technical routine competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 21 with the preliminary round in the morning and the final in the evening session.
The solo free routine competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 22 with the preliminary round and the final on July 24.
The duet free routine competition at 2013 World Aquatics Championships was held on July 23 with the preliminary round and the final on July 25.
/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2013_World_Aquatic: The women's 200 metre individual medley event in swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships took place on 28–29 July at the Palau Sant Jordi in Barcelona, Spain.
/wiki/Spain_at_the_2013_World_Aquatics_C: Spain competed at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships in Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain between 19 July and 4 August 2013 as the host nation.
